        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-03-09 08:00:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI was just testing this on master to verify that it works properly, but it seems there is something a bit wrong.  If one uses short options with arguments, but doesn't add a space, this is parsed badly:\n\n lfs_migrate -y -E1M -S1M -E10M -c4 /mnt/testfs/tt\n lfs migrate -E -1 -M -S -1 -M -E -1 -M -c -4 -c 1 -S 4194304 /mnt/testfs/tt\n\nso it is parsing every character as if it were a short option and not an argument.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "67b790fa987ac9aa5cb793e35128bdfec61e59cd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-04-10 18:05:52.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nWill not backport this to b2_10 at the current time.  There is a bug in this patch that causes problems with short options with arguments that do not have a space, like \"-E-1\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
